# Vue Data Flow & Composables

## Data flow

- Primary model: props down, events up
- Use `v-model` only for true two-way contracts
- Use `provide` / `inject` only for deep-tree or shared context
- Type contracts with `defineProps`, `defineEmits`, and `InjectionKey` when needed

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const props = defineProps<{ item: Item }>()
const emit = defineEmits<{ select: [id: string] }>()
</script>
```

## Composables

Extract into `useXxx()` when logic is reused, stateful, or side-effect heavy.

- Keep APIs small, typed, and predictable
- Separate feature logic from presentational components
- Return refs/computed explicitly; avoid leaking internal mutable bags

```ts
// composables/useFeature.ts
export function useFeature() {
  const items = ref<Item[]>([])
  const count = computed(() => items.value.length)
  async function load() { /* ... */ }
  return { items, count, load }
}
```

## Optional features (only when required)

Do not add by default:

- Slots, fallthrough attrs, KeepAlive, Teleport, Suspense
- Transition / TransitionGroup / class- or state-driven animation
- Custom directives, async components, render functions, plugins
- App-wide stores (Pinia) only when state crosses feature boundaries
